{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, abusing their position as an accountant. However, considering the defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution, a lengthy prison sentence is unwarranted. A brief period of incarceration is necessary to reflect the seriousness of the fiduciary breach and serve as a general deterrent, followed by a period of supervised release or probation to ensure the remainder of the stolen funds are repaid and personal debts are managed lawfully.",
  "verdict": 4
}
